	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1366><span id= >Greylin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Per testing posted on the Cleric board (eqclerics.gameglow.com), haste has zero effect on proc rates (in terms of procs per minute).&nbsp;&nbsp;So haste items will increase your weapon melee DPS, but your proc DPS will remain unchanged.  As procs makes up the majority of clerical DPS, you're not getting much 'bang for the buck' with haste items (or spells).<br><br>Bottom line:  don't bother with haste items as a cleric - there are non-haste belts with much better stats.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
