	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=217051><span id=Scholar>eezergoode</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>46 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hate to say anything bad about EQ Clerics board, but this is untrue...&nbsp;&nbsp;As a ranger,  Ihave both my self-buff procs, and with my epic, I have a 40% perm haste... I proc just as often, PER SWING, as I did without haste....  I proc about avery 6th swing with call of sky.. same as i was before I got swifty.    Procs are not calculated on a timed basis.. .they are randomly checked on each swing.  So, you swing more often, you proc more often.  Most parsers used to check DPS don't even calculate the procs... It is dificult to check DPS based on procs.  But if you count how many swings between your procs, you will see that the proc DPS does indeed go up with haste.  If yo uonly proc twice per fight, you may still only proc twice per fight... but that is most likely because the mob is dead sooner...<br><br>Regardless of this, I can't see a caster or cleric getting this item on a guild raid.  But on a pickup raid,  I feel everyone who CAN use the item gets a chance to roll on the item.</p>&nbsp;<br>Alagrianna, 57 Ranger of Tunare, Morell Thule</td></td></tr>
